Amanda Khoza, News24 File (Karabo Ngoepe/News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Commissioner Road in Boksburg has been re-opened following a violent protest on Saturday morning, local police said.EMPD spokesperson, acting lieutenant colonel Kobeli Mokheseng, said protesters blockaded Commissioner Road between Du Preez and Old Elsburg from around 05:00.Rubble, stones and burning tyres were used during the demonstration by a group of people claiming to be living nearby.Mokheseng said metro police and the police K9 unit attended the scene where the group handed a letter of demands to the mayoral committee.The road was cleared at around 12:45 after the group handed over its letter of demand.The police were still monitoring the area.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.